Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` is not null.
- The length of the input array `nums` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The length of the input array `nums` is less than or equal to 10^5.
- The elements in the input array `nums` are integers.
- The elements in the input array `nums` are within the range of -10^9 to 10^9.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer.
- The output represents the minimum number of moves required to make all elements in the input array `nums` equal.
- Each move can increment or decrement an element of the array by 1.
- The answer will fit in a 32-bit integer.